1 AN ACT concerning counties; relating to citizens commissions on local
2 government; granting certain boards of county commissioners
3 discretion to create such commission; amending K.S.A. 19-2670 and
4 repealing the existing section.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. K.S.A. 19-2670 is hereby amended to read as follows: 19-
8 2670. There shall may be created and established a citizens commission on
9 local government in every county in this state having a population of more
10 than one hundred seventy thousand (170,000) and not more than two
11 hundred thousand (200,000). Such commission shall consist of:
12 (1)(a) The board of county commissioners of the county;
13 (2)(b) the governing body of all cities of the first class located in such
14 county;
15 (3)(c) the trustee of each township in such county;
16 (4)(d) the chairmen of the boards of education of all school districts
17 located in such county;
18 (5)(e) the chairmen of boards of public utilities of all cities located in
19 such county;
20 (6)(f) the chairmen of boards of all drainage districts located within
21 such county;
22 (7)(g) the mayors of all cities of the second and third class located in
23 such county; and
24 (8)(h) eighteen (18) persons who shall be selected and appointed by
25 the members hereinbefore provided described in paragraphs (a) through
26 (g). Such persons shall be residents of the county and shall not be officers
27 or employees of the county or any city, school district, township, board of
28 public utilities or drainage district.
29 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 19-2670 is hereby repealed.
30 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
31 publication in the statute book.

